message.content:
- Primary programming language: Java
- Primary development framework: Spring Boot (part of the Spring ecosystem; uses Spring Web, Spring Data JPA, Spring Security)

Why:
- pom.xml uses Maven and declares the parent org.springframework.boot:spring-boot-starter-parent (version 2.3.5.RELEASE) and spring-boot starter dependencies (spring-boot-starter-web, spring-boot-starter-data-jpa, spring-boot-starter-security), which identify a Spring Boot application.
- Project layout under src/main/java contains a top-level application class UrCodebinApiApplication.java and typical Spring packages (controllers, services, repository, security), consistent with a Spring Boot REST API.
- Dockerfile builds with a Maven + OpenJDK 11 image and runs the packaged jar with -Dspring.profiles.active=prod, confirming a Spring Boot executable jar artifact.

Additional notes:
- Java target is 11 (pom property java.version and Docker base image openjdk11).
- Build tool: Maven (pom.xml and Dockerfile running mvn package).
